      "description": "Offered here is a museum-quality 2004 BMW M3 (E46), a masterclass in atmospheric induction and chassis dynamics. At its heart lies the S54B32 power plant, featuring six individual throttle bodies and an 8,000-RPM redline, delivering razor-sharp throttle response and a distinctive metallic rasp. The drivetrain is anchored by the coveted Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission, providing short, mechanical throws and precise engagement. Every bushing, link, and damper remains in peak operational condition, ensuring the near-perfect 50/50 weight distribution is fully realized through every corner. This example is mechanically flawless, with zero weeping from the constant pressure valve and a pristine, factory-reinforced rear subframe assembly. For the discerning collector seeking the zenith of the analog driving experience, this M3 is unparalleled in its preservation and performance integrity.",
